\section*{Projects}
\markright{Projects}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\begin{projects}

\item Locate the heating system in your dwelling, and find its 
      AFUE\index{Annual Fuel Utilization Efficiency (AFUE)} rating (furnace)
      or COP\index{coefficient of performance (COP)} (heat pump\index{heat pump}).
      If you were to replace your existing furnace with a furnace with a 
      98\% AFUE\index{Annual Fuel Utilization Efficiency (AFUE)}
      rating or heat pump\index{heat pump} with a COP\index{coefficient of performance (COP)} of 3.5,
      how much energy would you save annually?
      What is the price of that saved energy?
      What is the annual cost savings from this energy efficiency\index{energy efficiency} intervention?
      Assuming that the 98\% AFUE\index{Annual Fuel Utilization Efficiency (AFUE)} furnace or
      COP~$=$~3.5\index{coefficient of performance (COP)}
      heat pump\index{heat pump} lasts 20 years and 
      that you want to break even financially,
      what is the maximum price you should pay for 
      the upgraded furnace or heat pump\index{heat pump}?
      Does your answer change if you apply a discount rate 
      to the financial considerations of this project?

\item Locate the air conditioner in you dwelling, and find its SEER\index{seasonal energy efficiency ratio (SEER)}.
      If you were to replace your existing air conditioner 
      with an air conditioner with a SEER\index{seasonal energy efficiency ratio (SEER)} of 40
      (near the maximum SEER\index{seasonal energy efficiency ratio (SEER)} rating as of this writing),
      how much energy would you save annually?
      What is the price of that saved energy?
      What is the annual cost savings from this energy efficiency\index{energy efficiency} intervention?
      Assuming that the 40 SEER\index{seasonal energy efficiency ratio (SEER)} air conditioner lasts 15 years and 
      that you want to break even financially,
      what is the maximum price you should pay for a 40 
      SEER\index{seasonal energy efficiency ratio (SEER)} air conditioner?
      Does your answer change if you apply a discount rate 
      to the financial considerations of this project?

\item Rank the U-factor\index{U-factor} and solar heat gain coefficient 
      (SHGC)\index{solar heat gain coefficient (SHGC)}
      for single-, double-, and triple-paned windows\index{windows}.
      Does the ranking make sense?
      Rank the costs of the windows\index{window}.

\item If you are a college or university student,
      write a letter to your future self that describes
      the household in which you want to live.
      What is the size of the dwelling?
      How many people will live in it?
      What are its sustainability features?

\item Investigate energy retrofitting and recomissioning for buildings.
      What is the purpose of these activities?
      How do they contribute to sustainability?
      What would be the effect on household emissions if every home in the U.S.\
      were retrofitted with higher-efficiency appliances and more insulation\index{insulation}?
      
\item With reference to \ref{question:household_policies},
      make a sustainability-related benefits/drawbacks ledger for each policy, 
      being sure to identify areas where sustainability would be enhanced and 
      places where sustainability would be diminished.
      Be sure to address all three areas of sustainability, 
      social\index{social sustainability},
      environmental\index{environmental sustainability}, and 
      economic\index{economic sustainability}.
      After creating the ledger, 
      rethink your initial reactions to the policies.
      Now which policies would you welcome?
      Which would you resist?
      Why?
      
      For example, if all clothes washing\index{clothes washer} were to be done 
      at laundromats\index{laundromat}, there could be social benefits where
      laundromats\index{laundromat} would become a sort of ``town square''
      where neighbors meet to discuss municipal affairs as they do their laundry.
      On the other hand, time lost to commuting to the laundromat\index{laundromat} 
      might mean that other relationships suffer.
      If all clothes\index{clothing} were laundered at laundromats\index{laundromat}, 
      fewer washers\index{clothes washer} and dryers\index{clothes dryer}
      would be needed, resulting in less energy\index{embodied energy} and CO$_2$ embodied\index{embodied carbon} 
      in the stock of laundry equipment.
      But laundromats\index{laundromat} will likely have larger
      commercial washers\index{clothes washer} and dryers\index{clothes dryer}. 
      Would they be less energy efficient than smaller domestic washers\index{clothes washer} and dryers\index{clothes dryer}?
      Many people will need to drive to laundromats\index{laundromat} to do laundry, increasing transport-related
      CO$_2$ emissions\index{CO$_2$ emissions!transportation}.
      Finally, washers\index{clothes washer} and dryers\index{clothes dryer}
      would no longer be purchased, thereby saving money. 
      But the marginal cost of a load of laundry may be higher at a laundromat\index{laundromat} compared 
      to home-based laundry. 
      Is it a long-term financial benefit to do all your laundry at a laundromat\index{laundromat}? 
      How does the financial calculus change when the financial value of time is considered?
      
\item Cascade\index{Cascade} (a Proctor \& Gamble brand and a manufacturer of automatic dishwasher\index{dishwasher}
      detergent) did a study that shows it takes an average
      person 15 seconds to wash a dish ``by hand.'' Assuming an average water flow
      from the faucet of two gallons per minute and an Energy Star\index{Energy Star} automatic dishwasher\index{dishwasher}
      using 4 gallons of water per cycle, Cascade\index{Cascade} concluded that it is more
      efficient to run the dishwasher\index{dishwasher} with only eight dishes than to wash them by hand.
      (Note they were not advocating running near-empty loads, only that the break-even
      point was a very low number of dishes.)
      Measure your sink's flow rate and time yourself washing a variety of types of dishes.
      What is your break-even point?
      What is your break-even point for buying a new dishwasher\index{dishwasher}?
      
\item Find all the incandescent\index{incandescent lamp} and
      compact fluorescent lamps\index{CFL lamp} in your dwelling, and 
      consider changing to LEDs\index{LED lamp}.
      Be sure to choose LEDs\index{LED lamp} with similar lumen output so there will be minimal change
      in lighting service\index{lighting service} provided.
      What is the cost to purchase and install the new lamps.
      How much energy will be saved annually?
      How much CO$_2$ emissions\index{CO$_2$ emissions!lighting} will be saved annually?
      How much energy cost will be saved annually?
      What is the expected economic payback time?
      Should you replace your lamps?
      Why or why not?
      
\end{projects}



